sections.text:
# S6 Quasi Steady State Approximation 

![img-20.jpeg](img-20.jpeg)

Fig. S9: $\mathrm{P}_{2} \mathrm{Y}_{1}$ reaction diagram without a quasi steady state approximation. Four states are added on top of the model used in Purvis et al. [12], $\mathrm{p}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}, \mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}, \mathrm{p}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}$, and $\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}$ These states correspond to a desensitized receptor mediated by PKC .

We briefly outline the process of reducing the number of equations in Purvis et al. [12] by utilizing a quasi steady state (QSS) assumption. The work here is for the $\mathrm{P}_{2} \mathrm{Y}_{1}$ receptor only; the exact same computation can be done to the $\mathrm{P}_{2} \mathrm{Y}_{12}$ receptor to yield analogous equations. Figure S9 shows the entire reaction diagram for the $\mathrm{P}_{2} \mathrm{Y}_{1}$ receptor. It is generally assumed for G-protein coupled receptors that the receptors must be in an "active" conformation in order to process G protein [7]. Our assumption is that the receptor in the "active" conformation is in a quasi-steady state equilibrium with the corresponding "inactive" conformation, showed by the grey boxes in the figure. Under this assumption (to be made more precise below), we can reduce the number of equations by six

Below, we write out each of the 12 equations that are contained in the grey boxes in Figure S9. For concision, we divide all terms by $S_{\mathrm{PM}}$. The full equations are as follows:

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{d}{d t}\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}=\underbrace{-\frac{1}{k_{\mathrm{act}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}+k_{-\mathrm{act}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S}}_{\text {activation }}-\underbrace{k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}[\mathrm{ADP}]+k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}_{\text {ADP Binding }} \\

$$

& \frac{d}{d t}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}= & \underbrace{\alpha \beta \delta k_{\mathrm{act}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}-\left.k_{-\mathrm{act}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}\right]_{\text {activation }} \\

$$

If we make the assumption that $k_{\text {act }}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}$ is large compared to other reaction rates (i.e. $k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}$ and $k_{-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}$ ) under the condition that $k_{-\mathrm{act}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} / k_{\mathrm{act}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}=K_{\mathrm{act}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}$ is constant, then Equations 85, 93, 89, and 95 reduce to the following algebraic relationships:

$$
\begin{aligned}
{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S} } & =K_{\mathrm{act}}\left[\mathrm{P}_{2} \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S} \\
{\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S} } & =\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S} \\
{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} } & =\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} \\
{\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} } & =\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} \\
{\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S} } & =\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S} \\
{\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} } & =\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}
\end{aligned}
$$

We then define the concentrations $\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}=\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S}+\left[\mathrm{P}_{2} \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}$, and similar for the other three equations above. Plugging in the above equations into these definitions yield the following relations:

$$
\begin{aligned}
& {\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S}=\frac{K_{\mathrm{act}}}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}=\frac{1}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S}=\frac{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}=\frac{1}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}=\frac{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}=\frac{1}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}=\frac{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}=\frac{1}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S}=\frac{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}=\frac{1}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}=\frac{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}} \\
& {\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}=\frac{1}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\left[\overline{\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}}
\end{aligned}
$$

Finally, we compute $\frac{d}{d t}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}$ by adding the derivatives of $\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}\right]_{S}$ and $\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}$ and substituting for $\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}$ (and equivalently for the other reduced states):

$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{d}{d t}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}= & -\left(k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{1}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{ADP}\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}\right.\right. \\
& +\left(k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{1}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S} \\
& -\left(\beta k_{\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{1}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}\right.\right. \\
& +\left(k_{-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S} \\
& -\left(k_{\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{K_{\mathrm{act}}}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}\right.\right. \\
& \left.\left.+k_{-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}\right]_{S}\right.
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{d}{d t}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}= & \left(k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{1}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+\alpha k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{K_{\mathrm{act}}}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{ADP}\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}\right.\right. \\
& -\left(k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{1}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S} \\
& -\left(\beta k_{\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}\right. \\
& \left.+\left(\frac{k_{-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}}{\delta \gamma} \frac{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha \beta \delta k_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y} 1-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}\right. \\
& -\left(k_{\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}\right.\right. \\
& \left.\left.+k_{-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GTP}\right]_{S}\right. \\
& -k_{\mathrm{phos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\right]_{S}[\mathrm{PKCa}-\mathrm{Ca}-\mathrm{DAG}]+k_{\mathrm{dephos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \overline{\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}} \\
& \frac{d}{d t}\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}= & -\left(k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{1}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+\alpha k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{ADP}\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}}\right.\right. \\
& +\left(\frac{k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}}{\gamma} \frac{1}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+\frac{k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}}{\delta \gamma} \frac{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S} \\
& +\left(\beta k_{\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{K_{\mathrm{act}}}{K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}}\right.\right. \\
& -\left(k_{-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}}\right. \\
& \left.\left.+k_{\mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \mathrm{GDP}\left[\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}}\right]_{S}-\left(k_{-\mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S}\right.
\end{aligned}
$$

$$
\begin{aligned}
\frac{d}{d t}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}= & \left(k_{\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{1}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha \beta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\beta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{ADP}\right]\left[\overline{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}\right]_{S} \\
& -\left(\frac{k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}}{\gamma} \frac{1}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}+\frac{k_{-\mathrm{ADP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}}{\delta \gamma} \frac{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} \\
& \left(k_{\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha \beta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S} \\
& -\left(\frac{k_{-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}}{\delta \gamma} \frac{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha \beta \delta k_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y} 1-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} \\
& +k_{\mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\mathrm{GDP}\right]\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1} \mathrm{a}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}}\right]_{S} \\
& -\left(k_{-\mathrm{GDP}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}} \frac{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}}{\alpha \beta \delta K_{\mathrm{act}}+1}\right)\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y} 1-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} \\
& -k_{\mathrm{phos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}[\mathrm{PKCa}-\mathrm{Ca}-\mathrm{DAG}] \\
& +k_{\mathrm{dephos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S} \\
& \frac{d}{d t}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}= & k_{\mathrm{phos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S}\left[\mathrm{PKCa}-\mathrm{Ca}-\mathrm{DAG}\right]-k_{\mathrm{dephos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}\right]_{S} \\
& \frac{d}{d t}\left[\mathrm{ADP}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}= & k_{\mathrm{phos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}\left[\mathrm{PKCa}-\mathrm{Ca}-\mathrm{DAG}\right]-k_{\mathrm{dephos}}^{\mathrm{P} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}}\left[\overline{\mathrm{ADP}}-\mathrm{pP} 2 \mathrm{Y}_{1}-\mathrm{G}_{\mathrm{q}} \mathrm{GDP}\right]_{S}
\end{aligned}
$$

Which, after simplifying and dropping the bars and "a" from activated states, yields the equations in the earlier sections.

abstract:
Through experimental studies, many details of the pathway of integrin
$\alpha_{\rm IIb}\beta_3$ activation by ADP during the platelet aggregation
process have been mapped out. ADP binds to two separate G protein coupled
receptors on platelet surfaces, leading to alterations in the regulation of the
small GTPase RAP1. We seek to (1) gain insights into the relative contributions
of both pathways to RAP1-mediated integrin activation and to (2) predict
wildtype and mutated cell behavior in response to a continuous range of
external agonist concentrations. To this end, we develop a dynamical systems
model detailing the action of each protein in the two pathways up to the
regulation of RAP1. We perform a parameter estimation using flow cytometry data
to determine a number of unknown rate constants. We then validate with already
published data; in particular, the model confirmed the effect of impaired
P2Y$_1$ receptor desensitization or reduced RASA3 expression on RAP1
activation. We then predict the effect of protein expression levels on integrin
activation and show that components of the P2Y$_{12}$ pathway are critical to
the regulation of integrin. This model aids in our understanding of
interindividual variability in platelet response to ADP and therapeutic
P2Y$_{12}$ inhibition. It also provides a more detailed view of platelet
activation in the ongoing mathematical study of platelet aggregation.
